>Hi List,
>         I have read that Corvair spark-plug air-seals are "better" than
>original VW style ones.

They are a tremendous improvement!!!

>   Where does one go about purchasing them?

JC Whipme sells 'em.  They come in several EXCITING colors, in both
resistor and non-resistor types.  I use them on all of my VWs now.
Buy a couple of spare sets, while you're at it.  Maybe a different color,
for when you're in a different mood...........Buy the rest of your tune-up
stuff elsewhere, though.  I once got, from them, the shittiest set of points
and condenser that I've ever seen!

